251 ----
252 template ----
253 MDNodeOpsKey(const NodeTy *N, unsigned Offset = 0) 19 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
254 : Ops(N->op_begin() + Offset, N->op_end()), Hash(N->getHash()) {} 19 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
255 ----
256 template ----
257 bool compareOps(const NodeTy *RHS, unsigned Offset = 0) const { 0
258 if (getHash() != RHS->getHash()) 0
259 return false; 0
260 ----
261 assert((RawOps.empty() || Ops.empty()) && "Two sets of operands?"); 0
262 return RawOps.empty() ? compareOps(Ops, RHS, Offset) 0
263 : compareOps(RawOps, RHS, Offset); 0
264 } ----
265 ----
266 static unsigned calculateHash(MDNode *N, unsigned Offset = 0); ----
267 ----
268 private: ----
269 template ----
270 static bool compareOps(ArrayRef Ops, const MDNode *RHS, unsigned Offset) { 0
271 if (Ops.size() != RHS->getNumOperands() - Offset) 0
272 return false; 0
273 return std::equal(Ops.begin(), Ops.end(), RHS->op_begin() + Offset); 0
274 } ----
275 ----
276 static unsigned calculateHash(ArrayRef Ops); ----
277 ----
278 public: ----
279 unsigned getHash() const { return Hash; } 37 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
280 }; ----

363 template <> struct MDNodeKeyImpl { ----
364 Metadata *CountNode; ----
365 Metadata *LowerBound; ----
366 Metadata *UpperBound; ----
367 Metadata *Stride; ----
368 ----
369 MDNodeKeyImpl(Metadata *CountNode, Metadata *LowerBound, Metadata *UpperBound, 0
370 Metadata *Stride) ----
371 : CountNode(CountNode), LowerBound(LowerBound), UpperBound(UpperBound), 0
372 Stride(Stride) {} 0
373 MDNodeKeyImpl(const DISubrange *N) 0
374 : CountNode(N->getRawCountNode()), LowerBound(N->getRawLowerBound()), 0
375 UpperBound(N->getRawUpperBound()), Stride(N->getRawStride()) {} 0
376 ----
377 bool isKeyOf(const DISubrange *RHS) const { 0
378 auto BoundsEqual = [=](Metadata *Node1, Metadata *Node2) -> bool { 0
379 if (Node1 == Node2) 0
380 return true; 0
381 ----
382 ConstantAsMetadata *MD1 = dyn_cast_or_null(Node1); 0
383 ConstantAsMetadata *MD2 = dyn_cast_or_null(Node2); 0
384 if (MD1 && MD2) { 0
385 ConstantInt *CV1 = cast(MD1->getValue()); 0
386 ConstantInt *CV2 = cast(MD2->getValue()); 0
387 if (CV1->getSExtValue() == CV2->getSExtValue()) 0
388 return true; 0
389 } ----
390 return false; 0
391 }; ----
392 ----
393 return BoundsEqual(CountNode, RHS->getRawCountNode()) && 0
394 BoundsEqual(LowerBound, RHS->getRawLowerBound()) && 0
395 BoundsEqual(UpperBound, RHS->getRawUpperBound()) && 0
396 BoundsEqual(Stride, RHS->getRawStride()); 0
397 } ----
398 ----
399 unsigned getHashValue() const { 0
400 if (CountNode) 0
401 if (auto *MD = dyn_cast(CountNode)) 0
402 return hash_combine(cast(MD->getValue())->getSExtValue(), 0
403 LowerBound, UpperBound, Stride); 0
404 return hash_combine(CountNode, LowerBound, UpperBound, Stride); 0
405 } ----
406 }; ----

562 ExtraData(N->getRawExtraData()), Annotations(N->getRawAnnotations()) {} 0
563 ----
564 bool isKeyOf(const DIDerivedType *RHS) const { 0
565 return Tag == RHS->getTag() && Name == RHS->getRawName() && 0
566 File == RHS->getRawFile() && Line == RHS->getLine() && 0
567 Scope == RHS->getRawScope() && BaseType == RHS->getRawBaseType() && 0
568 SizeInBits == RHS->getSizeInBits() && 0
569 AlignInBits == RHS->getAlignInBits() && 0
570 OffsetInBits == RHS->getOffsetInBits() && 0
571 DWARFAddressSpace == RHS->getDWARFAddressSpace() && 0
572 Flags == RHS->getFlags() && ExtraData == RHS->getRawExtraData() && 0
573 Annotations == RHS->getRawAnnotations(); 0
574 } ----
575 ----
576 unsigned getHashValue() const { 0
577 // If this is a member inside an ODR type, only hash the type and the name. ----
578 // Otherwise the hash will be stronger than ----
579 // MDNodeSubsetEqualImpl::isODRMember(). ----
580 if (Tag == dwarf::DW_TAG_member && Name) 0
581 if (auto *CT = dyn_cast_or_null(Scope)) 0
582 if (CT->getRawIdentifier()) 0
583 return hash_combine(Name, Scope); 0
584 ----
585 // Intentionally computes the hash on a subset of the operands for ----
586 // performance reason. The subset has to be significant enough to avoid ----
587 // collision "most of the time". There is no correctness issue in case of ----
588 // collision because of the full check above. ----
589 return hash_combine(Tag, Name, File, Line, Scope, BaseType, Flags); 0
590 } ----
591 }; ----
592 ----
593 template <> struct MDNodeSubsetEqualImpl { ----
594 using KeyTy = MDNodeKeyImpl; ----
595 ----
596 static bool isSubsetEqual(const KeyTy &LHS, const DIDerivedType *RHS) { 0
597 return isODRMember(LHS.Tag, LHS.Scope, LHS.Name, RHS); 0
598 } ----
599 ----
600 static bool isSubsetEqual(const DIDerivedType *LHS, 0
601 const DIDerivedType *RHS) { ----
602 return isODRMember(LHS->getTag(), LHS->getRawScope(), LHS->getRawName(), 0
603 RHS); 0
604 } ----
605 ----
606 /// Subprograms compare equal if they declare the same function in an ODR ----
607 /// type. ----
608 static bool isODRMember(unsigned Tag, const Metadata *Scope, 0
609 const MDString *Name, const DIDerivedType *RHS) { ----
610 // Check whether the LHS is eligible. ----
611 if (Tag != dwarf::DW_TAG_member || !Name) 0
612 return false; 0
613 ----
614 auto *CT = dyn_cast_or_null(Scope); 0
615 if (!CT || !CT->getRawIdentifier()) 0
616 return false; 0
617 ----
618 // Compare to the RHS. ----
619 return Tag == RHS->getTag() && Name == RHS->getRawName() && 0
620 Scope == RHS->getRawScope(); 0
621 } ----
622 }; ----

839 template <> struct MDNodeSubsetEqualImpl { ----
840 using KeyTy = MDNodeKeyImpl; ----

843 return isDeclarationOfODRMember(LHS.isDefinition(), LHS.Scope, 0
844 LHS.LinkageName, LHS.TemplateParams, RHS); 0
845 } ----
846 ----
847 static bool isSubsetEqual(const DISubprogram *LHS, const DISubprogram *RHS) { 0
848 return isDeclarationOfODRMember(LHS->isDefinition(), LHS->getRawScope(), 0
849 LHS->getRawLinkageName(), 0
850 LHS->getRawTemplateParams(), RHS); 0
851 } ----
852 ----
853 /// Subprograms compare equal if they declare the same function in an ODR ----
854 /// type. ----
855 static bool isDeclarationOfODRMember(bool IsDefinition, const Metadata *Scope, 0
856 const MDString *LinkageName, ----
857 const Metadata *TemplateParams, ----
858 const DISubprogram *RHS) { ----
859 // Check whether the LHS is eligible. ----
860 if (IsDefinition || !Scope || !LinkageName) 0
861 return false; 0
862 ----
863 auto *CT = dyn_cast_or_null(Scope); 0
864 if (!CT || !CT->getRawIdentifier()) 0
865 return false; 0
866 ----
867 // Compare to the RHS. ----
868 // FIXME: We need to compare template parameters here to avoid incorrect ----
869 // collisions in mapMetadata when RF_ReuseAndMutateDistinctMDs and a ----
870 // ODR-DISubprogram has a non-ODR template parameter (i.e., a ----
871 // DICompositeType that does not have an identifier). Eventually we should ----
872 // decouple ODR logic from uniquing logic. ----
873 return IsDefinition == RHS->isDefinition() && Scope == RHS->getRawScope() && 0
874 LinkageName == RHS->getRawLinkageName() && 0
875 TemplateParams == RHS->getRawTemplateParams(); 0
876 } ----
877 }; ----

1060 ----
1061 MDNodeKeyImpl(Metadata *Scope, MDString *Name, MDString *LinkageName, 0
1062 Metadata *File, unsigned Line, Metadata *Type, ----
1063 bool IsLocalToUnit, bool IsDefinition, ----
1064 Metadata *StaticDataMemberDeclaration, Metadata *TemplateParams, ----
1065 uint32_t AlignInBits, Metadata *Annotations) ----
1066 : Scope(Scope), Name(Name), LinkageName(LinkageName), File(File), 0

1068 IsDefinition(IsDefinition), 0

1070 TemplateParams(TemplateParams), AlignInBits(AlignInBits), 0
1071 Annotations(Annotations) {} 0
1072 MDNodeKeyImpl(const DIGlobalVariable *N) 0
1073 : Scope(N->getRawScope()), Name(N->getRawName()), 0
1074 LinkageName(N->getRawLinkageName()), File(N->getRawFile()), 0
1075 Line(N->getLine()), Type(N->getRawType()), 0
1076 IsLocalToUnit(N->isLocalToUnit()), IsDefinition(N->isDefinition()), 0
1077 StaticDataMemberDeclaration(N->getRawStaticDataMemberDeclaration()), 0
1078 TemplateParams(N->getRawTemplateParams()), 0
1079 AlignInBits(N->getAlignInBits()), Annotations(N->getRawAnnotations()) {} 0
1080 ----
1081 bool isKeyOf(const DIGlobalVariable *RHS) const { 0
1082 return Scope == RHS->getRawScope() && Name == RHS->getRawName() && 0
1083 LinkageName == RHS->getRawLinkageName() && 0
1084 File == RHS->getRawFile() && Line == RHS->getLine() && 0
1085 Type == RHS->getRawType() && IsLocalToUnit == RHS->isLocalToUnit() && 0
1086 IsDefinition == RHS->isDefinition() && 0
1087 StaticDataMemberDeclaration == 0
1088 RHS->getRawStaticDataMemberDeclaration() && 0
1089 TemplateParams == RHS->getRawTemplateParams() && 0
1090 AlignInBits == RHS->getAlignInBits() && 0
1091 Annotations == RHS->getRawAnnotations(); 0
1092 } ----
1093 ----
1094 unsigned getHashValue() const { 0
1095 // We do not use AlignInBits in hashing function here on purpose: ----
1096 // in most cases this param for local variable is zero (for function param ----
1097 // it is always zero). This leads to lots of hash collisions and errors on ----
1098 // cases with lots of similar variables. ----
1099 // clang/test/CodeGen/debug-info-257-args.c is an example of this problem, ----
1100 // generated IR is random for each run and test fails with Align included. ----
1101 // TODO: make hashing work fine with such situations ----

1411 class LLVMContextImpl { ----
1412 public: ----
1413 /// OwnedModules - The set of modules instantiated in this context, and which ----

1425 /// The minimum hotness value a diagnostic needs in order to be included in ----
1426 /// optimization diagnostics. ----
1427 /// ----
1428 /// The threshold is an Optional value, which maps to one of the 3 states: ----
1429 /// 1). 0 => threshold disabled. All emarks will be printed. ----
1430 /// 2). positive int => manual threshold by user. Remarks with hotness exceed ----
1431 /// threshold will be printed. ----
1432 /// 3). None => 'auto' threshold by user. The actual value is not ----
1433 /// available at command line, but will be synced with ----
1434 /// hotness threhold from profile summary during ----
1435 /// compilation. ----
1436 /// ----
1437 /// State 1 and 2 are considered as terminal states. State transition is ----
1438 /// only allowed from 3 to 2, when the threshold is first synced with profile ----
1439 /// summary. This ensures that the threshold is set only once and stays ----
1440 /// constant. ----
1441 /// ----
1442 /// If threshold option is not specified, it is disabled (0) by default. ----
